name: Mushrooms of Russia. Leccinum percandidum
description:
White boletus (Latin Leccinum percandidum) is an edible mushroom of the genus Leccinum (Obabok) (Latin Leccinum) from the Boletaceae family (Latin Boletaceae). Sometimes it is considered a type of boletus. It is included in the Red Book of Russia.
